Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer* role with *Adtran Networks*. I bring over three years of professional experience in software development, system design, and automation, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the object-oriented, multithreaded software design, and Python development depth this position demands. At Sperse, I architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system in Python, applying object-oriented and multithreaded design principles to coordinate parallel workflows reliably — including careful management of inter-thread communication and agent concurrency to reduce end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50%. I also built a full observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks, enabling me to systematically debug and troubleshoot system failures in production. At Qualitest, I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO — demonstrating the kind of functional and object-oriented coding practices this role requires. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform and developed AWS Step Functions workflows to manage long-running jobs with correct execution sequencing and reliable inter-service communication. Together, these roles have prepared me to design, integrate, verify, and troubleshoot software systems, and to contribute meaningfully to Adtran's embedded software engineering responsibilities.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in systems-level programming, software verification, and technical communication — skills that align directly with the engineering discipline and collaborative culture Adtran values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the full development lifecycle — from system design through training, inference optimization, and deployment — requiring rigorous verification of software functionality at each stage. I also led workshops on GPU programming and AI Agents for 50+ students, developing the ability to communicate complex technical concepts clearly. This reflects Adtran's "Take Ownership" value: taking initiative end-to-end from conception through delivery.

I have always been passionate about making communications simpler and more affordable for everyone, everywhere, and enabling the world's software infrastructure to become more connected and accessible. I am excited to contribute my Python, multithreaded design, and systems engineering experience toward Adtran's goal of being the trusted partner for software-driven networking. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

